8 (9) (8) At the time of installation, a premanufactured unit
9 with a certificate of acceptability is subject only to the
10 nondestructive tests approved by the department necessary to
11 determine that it has not been damaged in transit or installation,
12 and that it has been installed in accordance with the building
13 permit and construction regulations.
14 (10) (9) The fees established for a building permit when the
15 application specifies use of a premanufactured unit with a
16 certificate of acceptability, or for inspection of the installation
17 of the premanufactured unit, shall must bear a reasonable relation
18 to the costs incurred by the enforcing agency in issuing a permit
19 or performing an inspection.
20 (11) (10) Notwithstanding any other provision of this section,
21 an enforcing agency may object to use of a premanufactured unit
22 with a certificate of acceptability on the basis that because the
23 premanufactured unit does not comply with the code. If an enforcing
24 agency on receipt of an application for a building permit
25 specifying the use of a premanufactured unit does object, objects
26 to use of the premanufactured unit, it may set forth its objections
27 in writing to the department before issuance of a building permit
28 and within not later than 10 business days after receipt of the
29 application. Within Not later than 10 business days after receipt
