1 of the objections, the commission, or a panel of 3 or more members
2 designated for that purpose by its chairman, chairperson, shall
3 hold a hearing on the objections in accordance with rules
4 promulgated by the department. After the hearing, the commission,
5 or its panel, within not later than 3 business days after the
6 hearing shall determine 1 of the following:
7 (a) The premanufactured unit does not comply with the code and
8 order that the certificate of acceptability be voided.
9 (b) The premanufactured unit requires additional testing and
10 evaluation in which case the testing and evaluation shall must be
11 conducted in accordance with this section.
12 (c) The objections are not valid and order the enforcing
13 agency to issue the building permit within not later than 3
14 business days after the order.
15 (12) (11) A certificate of acceptability issued by the
16 department shall must not be used for advertising purposes.
